# Ganeti

[[!img ganeti-logo.png alt="Ganeti logo" class="projectlogo" link="no"]]

[Ganeti](http://www.ganeti.org/) is a virtual machine cluster management tool built on top of existing virtualization technologies such as Xen or KVM and other open source software. Ganeti requires pre-installed virtualization software on your servers in order to function. Once installed, the tool assumes management of the virtual instances (Xen DomU). Ganeti controls

* Disk creation management,
* Operating system installation for instances (in co-operation with OS-specific install scripts), and
* Startup, shutdown, and failover between physical systems.

Ganeti is designed to facilitate cluster management of virtual servers and to provide fast and simple recovery after physical failures using commodity hardware.

